# repos.register — declarative list of repositories that should exist.
#
# provision-repos.sh (run by schedrunner on the Mac) reads this file and, for
# each entry whose repo does NOT yet exist on GitHub, creates it: scaffolds
# starter files (CLAUDE.md, README.md, .gitignore) under ~/Dropbox/Source/<name>,
# then creates + pushes the repo. Repos that already exist are left untouched,
# so this is a manifest of desired repos, not a queue you have to clean up.
#
# Format (| delimited):
#   name|visibility|type|description
#     name        repo + local dir name (under ~/Dropbox/Source/)
#     visibility  private | public         (default: private)
#     type        generic | python | node  (default: generic; controls .gitignore)
#     description one line; no '|' characters
#
# Lines beginning with # and blank/malformed lines are ignored. The /new-repo
# skill prompts for these fields and appends a line here for you.

ha-events|private|generic|Home Assistant events.
